records.addlTxt: Cases 22CF160, 22CM69, 22CT46, & 22TR1459 called @ 10:16 AM: Defendant Curtis P. Jelinski in court, in custody. Attorney Morgan Rae in court for Curtis P. Jelinski. Attorney Matthew R. Leusink in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant advised of potential punishment. As to 22CT46: Amended Complaint filed. Receipt admitted - Reading waived. Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant. Plea colloquy entertained. Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: 22CF160 - Counts 3 & 4 - NC. 22CM69 - Count 1 - NC. 22CT46 - Count 1 - NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. 22CF160 - Counts 2 & 5 - DRI. 22CM69 - Count 2 - DRI. 22CT46 - Count 2 - Dismissed Outright. 22TR1459 - DRI. Court orders: As to all matters - S/W - 2 years probation. Conditions: As to all counts - AODA and follow through. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Defendant is to successfully complete, to graduation, the Waushara County Treatment Court Program. As to 22CF160 Counts 3 & 4 and 22CM69 Count 1: Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. As to 22CT46 Count 1: 60 days WC Jail, GT. 42 days CFTS. $600 fine plus costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. $42.50 Blood Draw Fee. Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. As to Count 1 in case 22CF160: Defendant advised of potential punishment. Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant. Plea colloquy entertained. Collateral consequences explained. Consequences explained for failure to abide by terms of PPDA. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: NC. Court accepts plea and stays JOC. Court accepts terms and conditions of PPDA. Matter stayed for 2 years. Defendant is to successfully complete, to graduation, the Waushara County Treatment Court Program. The Court reminds the defendant that bond remains in effect throughout the pendency of the PPDA. Appeal rights given.
